title: Metro State Cycling Roadrunner Time Trial
Mesa State College - Mad Cow Classic Presented by:
Grand Junction, CO Criterium Series
description:
Grand Junction, CO Criterium Series
6 race series March 31, April 7,14,21,28,May 5th, 2010
Two Races will be held: 5:45pm - Group A - Men/Women Cat 1,2,3, Masters and Collegiate. 
6:45pm - Group B - Men/Women Cat 4,5, Masters and Collegiate
registration: To Register, please go to www.ascentproductions.net for mail in entry form and additional event information. You may also register day of for each race or the entire series.
notes:
Cost: $20 per race, $100.00 for all six races
Non-cash prizes awarded, points will be awarded for positions 1-10 overall.
directions: Race Start/Finish: Rocky Mountain Orthopedics, 627 25 1/2 Road, Grand Junction, CO 81505. From Patterson Rd. go North on 25 1/2 Rd. for 1/2 mile. Turn left at Fracture Lane, take immediate right into RMO parking lot.

description: Western State College Cycling Team presents the Mountaineer Open, an RMCCC collegiate race.
course: Riders will enjoy fast and flowing singe track mixed with variable and rocky terrain.
registration: Registration starts at 7:30 am at the base area of Hartman Rocks.
notes: The downhill courses will be on shuttled trails.  Each team needs to be prepared with their own shuttle vehicle, shuttles will not be provided.
directions: From Gunnison: West on highway 50, turn left on Gold Basin Road (follow brown signs), Hartman Rocks is on the right.
